HEADWORD: Pastorale
<hw>Pas`to*ra"le</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A composition in a soft, rural style,
generally in 6-8 or 12-8 time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of dance; a kind of figure used in a
dance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pastorally</ent>⟦br⟧
